  "prompt": "How do I apply driving license in Bangalore?",
  "response": "To apply for a driving license in Bangalore, follow these steps:\n\n1. Prerequisites:\n- Age: 18+ years\n- Valid identity proof\n- Address proof\n- Medical fitness certificate\n\n2. Documentation required:\n- Filled application form (Form RTO-1)\n- Proof of age (Birth certificate/School leaving certificate)\n- Proof of address\n- Passport size photographs\n- Medical fitness certificate\n- Proof of educational qualification\n- Learner's permit\n\n3. Process:\n- Visit Regional Transport Office (RTO) in Bangalore\n- Obtain application form (Form RTO-1)\n- Fill the form completely\n- Attach all necessary documents\n- Pay prescribed fees\n- Submit application\n- Undergo written test\n- Undergo practical driving test\n\n4. Online application steps:\n- Visit Sarathi Parivahan website\n- Create login\n- Fill Form RTO-1\n- Upload documents\n- Schedule driving test\n- Pay fees online\n\n5. Driving test locations:\n- Chancery Lane RTO\n- Banashankari RTO\n- Indiranagar RTO\n\nRecommended to check current guidelines and fees on official transport department website.",
